# Frontend Rules

Stack: Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, TanStack Query.

## Apps

- `apps/web` — dealer dashboard and mobile-first PWA for lot staff
- White-label as LotSync; never expose Minew or other vendor branding in UI

## UI Patterns

Every page needs: loading state, empty state, error state.
Use shadcn/ui for tables, cards, and forms.
Connect to the FastAPI backend via env `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`.

## Dashboard Routes (future)

Dashboard, Inventory, ESL Tags, Pairings, Sync Events, Price Mismatches, Inventory Sources, Label Templates, Settings.

## Mobile PWA (future)

Pairing requires two scans: VIN then ESL device code. Show vehicle confirmation before final pair. Do not allow pairing on manual text entry alone unless admin override.

## Security

- Frontend never sends arbitrary `dealership_id` for access control.
- No provider API credentials in browser code or env vars exposed to client.
